BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. Due to the Ashtabula Lakeside High School 4
building being unusable as a result of winter weather for which 5
the Governor declared a state of emergency, the Department of 6
Education and Workforce shall do both of the following for the 7
2024-2025 school year: 8
(1) Upon application from the Ashtabula City School 9
District and approval by the Department, waive the requirement 10
for a twelfth grade student who attended that school building to 11
complete the minimum hours of course instruction required to 12
earn the units required for high school graduation under section 13
3313.603 of the Revised Code if the student did not complete the 14
units as a result of the building being unusable; 15
(2) Waive the required minimum number of hours the school 16
building must be open for instruction with students in 17
attendance under section 3313.48 of the Revised Code for the 18
purposes of the school district's eligibility to receive state 19

